\par The inspector had got very red.
\par "So that was the game," he muttered. "Robbery. But I can't make it out. There's been no mention of these things being missing."
\par "Perhaps they haven't discovered the loss," I suggested. "I presume these valuable things would not have been kept out in common use. Colonel Protheroe probably kept them locked away in a safe."
\par "I must investigate this," said the inspector. "I'll go right up to Old Hall now. So that's 
